As President Muhammadu Buhari visits Ogun State on Thursday (today), the state government has announced the closure of some roads, while advising motorists to make use of alternative routes to get to their destinations. Buhari will be in Ogun to commission some projects of Governor Dapo Abiodun, while also using the opportunity to meet with some stakeholders. In a statement on Wednesday, the Ogun Traffic Compliance and Enforcement (TRACE) corps, said, “the newly reconstructed Abeokuta-Kobape-Siun-Sagamu interchange will be closed to traffic from 6am-4pm, while Ijebu/Ode-Mojoda-Epe Expressway will be closed to traffic from 6am-1pm.”